result.execSummary:
The defendant Brandon M Krzyzanowski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Fine to be paid at $50.00 per month commencing 07/01/15 and each month thereafter or penalty of 7 days jail for non-payment. 
Court waives the DNA Surcharge based on date of violation.

records.addlTxt: with Elements of criminal offenses to which plea is being entered.

Defendant Brandon M Krzyzanowski in court.  Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant states he wishes to accept state's offer and proceed pro se today.  Court performs colloquy with Defendant regarding his right to counsel.  Defendant proceeds pro se.  Defendant enters a no contest plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed and read-in. State gives sentencing recommendations.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  FINE: $363.25 (to be paid at $50.00 per month, commencing 7/1/15, alternate 7 days jail if not paid)  **Court waives the DNA Surcharge based on date of violation.**
Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.

Defendant Brandon M Krzyzanowski in court.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Court advises of right to an attorney.   NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT.
  Hearing scheduled for June 8, 2015 at 09:30 am.
